text: Lexington County is a county located in the U.S. state of South Carolina. As of the 2020 U.S. census, 293,991 people lived there. Its county seat and largest town is Lexington. The county was created in 1785. Its name commemorates the Battle of Lexington in the American Revolutionary War. == References == Category:1785 establishments in South Carolina Category:South Carolina counties
title: Lexington County, South Carolina
